The paper deals with the problem of interference in communication networks, which is a central topic in information theory (cs.IT). The specific focus is on interference networks, which are a type of network in which multiple transmitters and receivers interfere with each other (cs.NI). The paper also considers the Gaussian interference network, which is a specific type of interference network that is commonly studied in information theory (cs.SI). The paper uses mathematical techniques to derive achievable rate regions and sum rates, which suggests that it may belong to the mathematical methods sub-category (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of maximizing the sum rate, which is a central problem in communication networks and may suggest that it belongs to the communication and networking sub-category (cs.CC).
